[{"text": "Ladies and gentlemen, gather around.", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I would love to share with you a story.", "start": 17.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Once upon a time", "start": 20.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 19th century Germany,", "start": 22.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there was the book.", "start": 24.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now during this time,", "start": 26.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the book was the king of storytelling.", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was venerable.", "start": 30.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was ubiquitous.", "start": 32.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But it was a little bit boring.", "start": 34.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Because in its 400 years of existence,", "start": 38.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "storytellers never evolved the book", "start": 41.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a storytelling device.", "start": 43.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But then one author arrived,", "start": 45.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and he changed the game forever.", "start": 47.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 51.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "His name was Lothar,", "start": 53.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Lothar Meggendorfer.", "start": 55.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Lothar Meggendorfer put his foot down,", "start": 58.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and he said, \"Genug ist genug!\"", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He grabbed his pen,", "start": 67.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he snatched his scissors.", "start": 69.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This man refused to fold to the conventions of normalcy", "start": 71.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and just decided to fold.", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "History would know Lothar Meggendorfer", "start": 75.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as -- who else? --", "start": 77.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the world's first true inventor", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the children's pop-up book.", "start": 81.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 84.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "For this delight and for this wonder,", "start": 86.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "people rejoiced.", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Cheering)", "start": 90.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They were happy because the story survived,", "start": 93.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and that the world would keep on spinning.", "start": 96.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Lothar Meggendorfer wasn't the first", "start": 98.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to evolve the way a story was told,", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and he certainly wasn't the last.", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Whether storytellers realized it or not,", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they were channeling Meggendorfer's spirit", "start": 106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when they moved opera to vaudville,", "start": 108.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "radio news to radio theater,", "start": 113.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "film to film in motion", "start": 116.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to film in sound, color, 3D,", "start": 119.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on VHS and on DVD.", "start": 122.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There seemed to be no cure for this Meggendorferitis.", "start": 124.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And things got a lot more fun when the Internet came around.", "start": 127.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 130.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because, not only could people broadcast their stories throughout the world,", "start": 132.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but they could do so", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "using what seemed to be an infinite amount of devices.", "start": 137.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For example, one company", "start": 140.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "would tell a story of love", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "through its very own search engine.", "start": 145.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One Taiwanese production studio", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would interpret American politics in 3D.", "start": 152.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 155.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "And one man would tell the stories of his father", "start": 160.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "by using a platform called Twitter", "start": 164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to communicate the excrement his father would gesticulate.", "start": 166.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And after all this, everyone paused;", "start": 169.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they took a step back.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They realized that, in 6,000 years of storytelling,", "start": 173.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they've gone from depicting hunting on cave walls", "start": 176.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to depicting Shakespeare on Facebook walls.", "start": 180.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And this was a cause for celebration.", "start": 184.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The art of storytelling has remained unchanged.", "start": 187.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And for the most part, the stories are recycled.", "start": 189.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But the way that humans tell the stories", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has always evolved", "start": 194.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with pure, consistent novelty.", "start": 196.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they remembered a man,", "start": 199.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one amazing German,", "start": 201.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "every time a new storytelling device", "start": 204.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "popped up next.", "start": 208.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And for that,", "start": 210.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the audience --", "start": 212.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the lovely, beautiful audience --", "start": 214.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would live happily ever after.", "start": 216.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 219.26, "duration": 5.0}]